s are set. I wonder if native tests run separately from Gradle tests and what properties apply there. It seems that in GraalVM Native Image for JDK 21, the Security Manager isn't supported, leading to potential UOE when calling `System.setSecurityManager`. I’ll look into how existing tests manage security.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_lXiyVyHq9HVZBWKjZi9zobkV|fc_092092a8adfc46bf0169fa7b46ccfc8197be6ebc4c54068db2", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"setSecurityManager|SecurityManager|accessDeclaredMembers\" tests/src -n | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 921, "output": 1724, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31317, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778023213159, "responseId": "resp_092092a8adfc46bf0169fa7b2dbea08197929db8adbce36d5d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_lXiyVyHq9HVZBWKjZi9zobkV|fc_092092a8adfc46bf0169fa7b46ccfc8197be6ebc4c54068db2", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaMembersTest.java:85:        DeclaredMemberDenyingSecurityManager securityManager =\ntests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaMembersTest.java:86:                new DeclaredMemberDenyingSecurityManager();\ntests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaMembersTest.java:87:        SecurityManager previousSecurityManager = System.getSecurityManager();\ntests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaMembersTest.java:88:        boolean securityManagerInstalled = installSecurityManagerIfSupported(securityManager);\ntests/